<div class="intro-header">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="intro-message">
          <%= image_tag('ucalgary-logo.jpg', height: '200') %>
          <h1>The Fourth Annual PHAS Symposium</h1>
          <h3>February 20, 2019</h3>
          <hr class="intro-divder"/>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="instructions">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
        <p>
          It is our pleasure to invite you to the Fourth Annual Physics and Astronomy Symposium. The conference is organized by the PHAS Departmental Graduate Association and will take place at <strong>SB142 and SA109</strong> on the main campus of the University of Calgary on <strong>February 20, 2019</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
           The purpose of the PHAS Symposium is to bring together researchers from all PHAS groups to share their ongoing research. All PHAS graduate and undergraduate students and postdoctoral research fellows are welcome and encouraged to submit an abstract for an oral and/or a poster presentation. There is a $5 registration fee for both attendees and presenters. Lunch and coffee/refreshments will be provided, and there will be a social event in the evening at the Last Defence Lounge. Prizes will be given out for best talks and posters! Details of this and other DGA events are also available on our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/UCalgary-PHAS-DGA-1528636897397050/">Facebook page</a>.
        </p>
	
	<p>
           <strong>Abstract submission will be open soon!</strong>
        </p> 

	<p>
	We are pleased to announce two invited speakers for the Symposium: 
	<p>
	<strong>Dr J&ouml;rn Davidsen</strong>, Humboldt Research Fellow from the Department of Physics and Astronomy at the University of Calgary</li>
	</p>
	<p>
	J&ouml;rn Davidsen is a tenured associate professor with the Department of Physics and Astronomy here at the university. His current research focus is on physics of complex 	systems. Using applications of statistical and computational physics and modern network theory, he tackles a variety of problems, such as extreme events, seismicity and climate dynamics. Additionally, on the biology/chemistry front, he investigates defect-mediated turbulence, cardiac arrhythmia and neuronal firing patterns.
	</p>
	<p>
	<strong>Dr Greg Pierce</strong>, Medical Physicist at the Tom Baker Cancer Centre, and Adjunct Professor in the Department of Physics and Astronomy at the University of Calgary
	</p>
	<p>
	Dr. Greg Pierce has been a Radiation Oncology Medical Physicist at the Tom Baker Cancer Centre since 2013. He previously completed his Medical Physicist Residency in 		London, Ontario at the London Regional Cancer Program. His current research interests and work are the delivery of Total Body Irradiation for Bone Marrow Transplant.
	</p>
        </p>
    
        <p>
          We look forward to seeing you all at the Fourth Annual PHAS Symposium!
        </p>

        <p>
          Sincerely,
          </p>
          <p>
          <br/>
          <strong>The Organizing Committee</strong> (in alphabetical order):
          <br/>
          <br/>
          Faezeh Kimiaee Asadi
          <br/>
          Taylor Cameron
          <br/>
          Davor Curic
          <br/>
          Pamela Freeman
          <br/>
          Omid Khajehdehi
          <br/>
          Svetlana Kuznetsova
          <br/>
          Ayush Mandwal
          <br/>
          Hamza Qureshi
          <br/>
          Kyle Reiter
          <br/>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<hr/>



  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
       <h3>Undergraduate funding opportunity</h3>
       <p>
        The Physics and Astronomy Students' Association (PASA) is proud to announce funding support for any undergraduate who wishes to present a poster at the PHAS Symposium. The best 4 posters will be reimbursed for up to $40 (rush-order pricing cannot be fully funded).
       </p>
       <p>
        Applications can be submitted by email or in person to a PASA executive, and must include both the poster receipt and some proof of symposium acceptance. More information on the application deadline will be available soon.
       </p>
       <p>
        For more information or to submit an application, email physastr@ucalgary.ca. You can also drop in to our club room at ST 058/060 to talk with a friendly exec!
       </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr/>

<% flash.each do |name, msg| %>
  <%= content_tag :div, msg, class: (name == 'success' ? "bg-success" : "bg-danger") %>
<% end %>


<div class="content-section-a">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <%= form_for :submission, url: submissions_path, html: {class: 'form-horizontal'} do |f| %>
        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :presentation_type, class: 'col-sm-2 control-label required' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:presentation_type, "oral", checked: true, disabled: false) %>
              oral
            </label>
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:presentation_type, "poster", disabled: false) %>
              poster
            </label>
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:presentation_type, "attender", disabled: false) %>
              attender
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :name, class: 'col-sm-2 control-label required' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <%= f.text_field :name, class: 'form-control', placeholder: 'Name' %>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :email, class: 'col-sm-2 control-label required' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <%= f.text_field :email, class: 'form-control', placeholder: 'Email' %>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :attender_type, class: 'col-sm-2 control-label required' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:attender_type, "undergrad", checked: true) %>
              Undergraduate
            </label>
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:attender_type, "msc") %>
              MSc
            </label>
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:attender_type, "phd") %>
              PhD
            </label>
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:attender_type, "postdoc") %>
              Postdoctoral Fellow
            </label>
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:attender_type, "faculty") %>
              Faculty
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :sub_department, 'Group', class: 'col-sm-2 control-label required togglable' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <%= f.text_field :sub_department, class: 'form-control togglable', placeholder: 'Group (ex: IQST)', readonly: true %>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :co_authors, 'Co-Authors', class: 'col-sm-2 control-label toggalble' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <%= f.text_field :co_authors, class: 'form-control togglable', placeholder: 'Co-Authors (ex: Erwin Schr&ouml;dinger, Paul Dirac)'.html_safe %>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :title, class: 'col-sm-2 control-label required togglable' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <%= f.text_field :title, class: 'form-control togglable', placeholder: 'Title (250 character limit)' %>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :abstract, class: 'col-sm-2 control-label required togglable' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <%= f.text_area :abstract, class: 'form-control togglable', placeholder: 'Abstract (2000 character limit)' %>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr/>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :dietary_restrictions, class: 'col-sm-2 control-label' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <%= f.text_area :dietary_restrictions, class: 'form-control', placeholder: 'Dietary restrictions' %>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <%= f.label :will_attend_social_event, 'Do you plan to attend the social event?', class: 'col-sm-2 control-label' %>
          <div class="col-sm-10">
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:will_attend_social_event, 'true', checked: true) %>
              Yes
            </label>
            <label class="checkbox-inline">
              <%= f.radio_button(:will_attend_social_event, 'false') %>
              No
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">         
        <p>
         After you press submit, you will receive a confirmation email that includes information about how to submit your registration fee. 
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
        <br/>

        <div class='form-group'>
          <div class="col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-10">
            <%= f.submit 'Submit', class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% end %>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <p>Funding to make this symposium possible has been generously provided by the U of C GSA and the Physics and Astronomy Department.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<hr/>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <p>Please contact <%= link_to "kyle.reiter1@ucalgary.ca", "mailto:kyle.reiter1@ucalgary.ca" %> if you have any questions about the form.</p>
  </div>
</div>

